<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" type="siscussion">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="102">
Morphological characters, such as sepals persistent or deciduous, leaves glabrous or with white or brown hair, venation craspedodromous or camptodromous, styles free or connate, are of taxonomic significance and useful in classification and delimitation of simple-leaved 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Sorbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa (
<bibRefCitation author="Hedlund, T" journalOrPublisher="Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" pagination="1 - 147" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/34434617" refId="B3" refString="Hedlund, T, 1901. Monographie der Gattung Sorbus. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar 35: 1 - 147, https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/34434617" title="Monographie der Gattung Sorbus." url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/34434617" volume="35" year="1901">Hedlund 1901</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, TT" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" publicationUrl="http://frps.eflora.cn/frps/sorbus" refId="B7" refString="Yu, TT, Lu, LT, 1974. Spiraea, Dichotomanthes, Cotoneaster, Sorbus, Chaenomeles. In: Yu TT (Ed.) Flora Republicae Popularis Sinicae 36. Science Press, Beijing, http://frps.eflora.cn/frps/sorbus" title="Spiraea, Dichotomanthes, Cotoneaster, Sorbus, Chaenomeles. In: Yu TT (Ed.) Flora Republicae Popularis Sinicae 36." url="http://frps.eflora.cn/frps/sorbus" year="1974">Yu and Lu 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gabrielian, E" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" refId="B2" refString="Gabrielian, E, 1978. The genus Sorbus L. in Eastern Asia and the Himalayas. Yerevan: Armenian Academy of Sciences, 264 pp. [62 pls; in Russian, with English summary]" title="The genus Sorbus L. in Eastern Asia and the Himalayas. Yerevan: Armenian Academy of Sciences, 264 pp. [62 pls; in Russian, with English summary]" year="1978">Gabrielian 1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lu, LT" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="9. Rosaceae. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" pagination="144 - 170" publicationUrl="http://foc.eflora.cn/content.aspx?TaxonId=130718" refId="B4" refString="Lu, LT, Spongberg, SA, 2003. Sorbus Linnaeus. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Hong, DY, Eds., Flora of China, vol. 9. Rosaceae. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis: 144 - 170, http://foc.eflora.cn/content.aspx?TaxonId=130718" title="Sorbus Linnaeus." url="http://foc.eflora.cn/content.aspx?TaxonId=130718" volumeTitle="Flora of China, vol." year="2003">Lu and Spongberg 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Aldasoro, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" pagination="1 - 148" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/25027918" refId="B1" refString="Aldasoro, JJ, Aedo, C, Garmendia, FM, de la Hoz, FP, Navarro, C, 2004. Revision of Sorbus Subgenera Aria and Torminaria (Rosaceae - Maloideae). Systematic Botany Monographs 69: 1 - 148, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25027918" title="Revision of Sorbus Subgenera Aria and Torminaria (Rosaceae - Maloideae)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/25027918" volume="69" year="2004">Aldasoro et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
). In the latest revision of simple-leaved species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Sorbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Aldasoro, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" pagination="1 - 148" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/25027918" refId="B1" refString="Aldasoro, JJ, Aedo, C, Garmendia, FM, de la Hoz, FP, Navarro, C, 2004. Revision of Sorbus Subgenera Aria and Torminaria (Rosaceae - Maloideae). Systematic Botany Monographs 69: 1 - 148, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25027918" title="Revision of Sorbus Subgenera Aria and Torminaria (Rosaceae - Maloideae)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/25027918" volume="69" year="2004">Aldasoro et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
), species in China are assigned to one subgenus and five sections. The new species is morphologically a member of 
<taxonomicName authority="Persoon" genus="S." infraspecific-rank="sect." lsidName="S." pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="section" section="Alnifoliae" subGenus="Aria">S. subg. Aria Persoon sect. Alnifoliae</taxonomicName>
(Yu) Aldasoro et al., for it shares the common characters of this section, such as craspedodromous venation, spreading and white petals, coalescent styles and red pomes. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="sect." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Alnifoliae">Sorbus sect. Alnifoliae</taxonomicName>
contains five species: 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. alnifolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species" species="alnifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">S. alnifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. japonica" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">S. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Decne.) Hedl., 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. zahlbruckneri" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species" species="zahlbruckneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">S. zahlbruckneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C. K. Schneid., 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. yuana" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species" species="yuana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">S. yuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spongberg and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. folgneri" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species" species="folgneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">S. folgneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mainly distributed in China, Japan and Korea (
<bibRefCitation author="Aldasoro, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" pagination="1 - 148" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/25027918" refId="B1" refString="Aldasoro, JJ, Aedo, C, Garmendia, FM, de la Hoz, FP, Navarro, C, 2004. Revision of Sorbus Subgenera Aria and Torminaria (Rosaceae - Maloideae). Systematic Botany Monographs 69: 1 - 148, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25027918" title="Revision of Sorbus Subgenera Aria and Torminaria (Rosaceae - Maloideae)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/25027918" volume="69" year="2004">Aldasoro et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
). The new species is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. folgneri" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species" species="folgneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">S. folgneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in leaf form (Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Leaf abaxial surface of A Sorbus lushanensis and B S. folgneri, show the similar of leaf form and the differences of hairs." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.119.32148.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/277393" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">5</figureCitation>
) and the difference between the two species is summarised in Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Comparison of main features separating S. lushanensis and S. folgneri." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/C8431DFF785E52AD64CB9856D7861692" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" tableUuid="C8431DFF785E52AD64CB9856D7861692">1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
