<paragraph lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Xin Chen &amp; Jing Qiu" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus lushanensis" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lushanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Sorbus lushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the two sympatric species, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. alnifolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species" species="alnifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">S. alnifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. folgneri" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species" species="folgneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">S. folgneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are all diploid (2n=2x=34) sexual species (Chen et al. unpubl. data). Our preliminary 
<pageBreakToken pageId="6" pageNumber="103" start="start">molecular</pageBreakToken>
work, based on two chloroplast gene fragments, atpB-rbcL and trnL and four nuclear gene fragments, GBSSI, PGIP, PPO and WD, resolved that 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. lushanensis" pageId="6" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="lushanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="103">S. lushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed as sister to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="S. alnifolia var. angulata" pageId="6" pageNumber="103" rank="variety" species="alnifolia" variety="angulata">S. alnifolia var. angulata</taxonomicName>
S. B. Liang and they two together were resolved as sister to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. folgneri" pageId="6" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="folgneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="103">S. folgneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. lushanensis" pageId="6" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="lushanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="103">S. lushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not most closely related to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. folgneri" pageId="6" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="folgneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="103">S. folgneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Chen et al. unpubl. data). The new species can be distinguished from the other five species by its abaxially greenish-grey tomentose laminae.
</paragraph>
